parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The hot metal rails on the floor can cause burns and blisters, posing a safety risk to occupants, especially children.
symptoms: The metal rails on the floor get extremely hot
especially in the center near the second row.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sliding power doors may not reverse when hitting a person or object, posing a risk of injury or crushing.
symptoms: The doors do not stop closing unless excessive force is applied
and may not reverse even when hitting a person or object.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden shattering of the sunroof can cause injury or distraction while driving.
The vehicle shutting off while driving can cause loss of control, accidents, or strand the driver.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts off while driving
and may not accelerate at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden cracking of the windshield can cause distraction while driving and reduce visibility.
symptoms: and the crack can spread quickly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power sliding door sensor can cause the door to close on occupants, resulting in injuries, particularly to children, and potentially leading to crushing hazards.
symptoms: The door continues to close despite objects or body parts in its path
requiring excessive force to stop or reverse
and may not detect objects or limbs

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sliding door can cause injury or trapping of occupants, especially children, between the door and the B-pillar.
symptoms: The sliding door closes despite encountering resistance

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning rear door can pose a safety risk, especially in situations where the door remains open while the vehicle is in motion, increasing the risk of accidents or robberies.
symptoms: The rear door reopens after starting the car

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Vehicle Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of power and stalling of the vehicle can cause accidents, especially when driving at high speeds, and pose a significant safety risk to occupants.
symptoms: The vehicle cuts off in the middle of traffic
with no warning lights or codes displayed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a range of safety issues, including loss of motive power, brake failure, and power steering failure, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: and the vehicle loses motive power
with the brakes and power steering becoming inoperable.
